1021{
1022 ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnClick = 1 << 4, // return true on click (mouse down event)
1023 ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnClickRelease = 1 << 5, // [Default] return true on click + release on same item <-- this is what the majority of Button are using
1024 ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnClickReleaseAnywhere = 1 << 6, // return true on click + release even if the release event is not done while hovering the item
1025 ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnRelease = 1 << 7, // return true on release (default requires click+release)
1026 ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnDoubleClick = 1 << 8, // return true on double-click (default requires click+release)
1027 ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnDragDropHold = 1 << 9, // return true when held into while we are drag and dropping another item (used by e.g. tree nodes, collapsing headers)
1028 //ImGuiButtonFlags_Repeat = 1 << 10, // hold to repeat -> use ImGuiItemFlags_ButtonRepeat instead.
1029 ImGuiButtonFlags_FlattenChildren = 1 << 11, // allow interactions even if a child window is overlapping
1030 ImGuiButtonFlags_AllowOverlap = 1 << 12, // require previous frame HoveredId to either match id or be null before being usable.

1035 ImGuiButtonFlags_NoHoldingActiveId = 1 << 17, // don't set ActiveId while holding the mouse (ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnClick only)
1036 ImGuiButtonFlags_NoNavFocus = 1 << 18, // don't override navigation focus when activated (FIXME: this is essentially used every time an item uses ImGuiItemFlags_NoNav, but because legacy specs don't requires LastItemData to be set ButtonBehavior(), we can't poll g.LastItemData.ItemFlags)
1037 ImGuiButtonFlags_NoHoveredOnFocus = 1 << 19, // don't report as hovered when nav focus is on this item
1038 ImGuiButtonFlags_NoSetKeyOwner = 1 << 20, // don't set key/input owner on the initial click (note: mouse buttons are keys! often, the key in question will be ImGuiKey_MouseLeft!)
1039 ImGuiButtonFlags_NoTestKeyOwner = 1 << 21, // don't test key/input owner when polling the key (note: mouse buttons are keys! often, the key in question will be ImGuiKey_MouseLeft!)

1597{
1598 // Flags for IsKeyPressed(), IsKeyChordPressed(), IsMouseClicked(), Shortcut()
1599 // - Repeat mode: Repeat rate selection
1600 ImGuiInputFlags_RepeatRateDefault = 1 << 1, // Repeat rate: Regular (default)
1601 ImGuiInputFlags_RepeatRateNavMove = 1 << 2, // Repeat rate: Fast
1602 ImGuiInputFlags_RepeatRateNavTweak = 1 << 3, // Repeat rate: Faster
1603 // - Repeat mode: Specify when repeating key pressed can be interrupted.
1604 // - In theory ImGuiInputFlags_RepeatUntilOtherKeyPress may be a desirable default, but it would break too many behavior so everything is opt-in.
1605 ImGuiInputFlags_RepeatUntilRelease = 1 << 4, // Stop repeating when released (default for all functions except Shortcut). This only exists to allow overriding Shortcut() default behavior.
1606 ImGuiInputFlags_RepeatUntilKeyModsChange = 1 << 5, // Stop repeating when released OR if keyboard mods are changed (default for Shortcut)
1607 ImGuiInputFlags_RepeatUntilKeyModsChangeFromNone = 1 << 6, // Stop repeating when released OR if keyboard mods are leaving the None state. Allows going from Mod+Key to Key by releasing Mod.
1608 ImGuiInputFlags_RepeatUntilOtherKeyPress = 1 << 7, // Stop repeating when released OR if any other keyboard key is pressed during the repeat
1609
1610 // Flags for SetKeyOwner(), SetItemKeyOwner()
1611 // - Locking key away from non-input aware code. Locking is useful to make input-owner-aware code steal keys from non-input-owner-aware code. If all code is input-owner-aware locking would never be necessary.
1612 ImGuiInputFlags_LockThisFrame = 1 << 20, // Further accesses to key data will require EXPLICIT owner ID (ImGuiKeyOwner_Any/0 will NOT accepted for polling). Cleared at end of frame.
1613 ImGuiInputFlags_LockUntilRelease = 1 << 21, // Further accesses to key data will require EXPLICIT owner ID (ImGuiKeyOwner_Any/0 will NOT accepted for polling). Cleared when the key is released or at end of each frame if key is released.

2453 // Previously we used ImTextCountCharsFromUtf8/ImTextStrFromUtf8 here but we now need to support ImWchar16 and ImWchar32!

2458 // We don't rely on current ImGuiContext as this is implied to be a helper function which doesn't depend on it (see #7314).

2460 ImVector<wchar_t> local_temp_heap;

5123 // Set UV from packed rectangle

5129 glyph->V0 = (r->y) * atlas->TexUvScale.y;
5130 glyph->U1 = (r->x + r->w) * atlas->TexUvScale.x;

5145 glyph->X1 += char_off_x;

3811 {
3812 ImFontBaked* closest_larger_match = NULL;
3813 ImFontBaked* closest_smaller_match = NULL;
3814 for (int baked_n = 0; baked_n < builder->BakedPool.Size; baked_n++)

5322 ImFontBaked** p_baked_in_map = (ImFontBaked**)builder->BakedMap.GetVoidPtrRef(baked_id);
5323 ImFontBaked* baked = *p_baked_in_map;
5324 if (baked != NULL)
5325 {
5326 IM_ASSERT(baked->Size == font_size && baked->ContainerFont == font && baked->BakedId == baked_id);
5327 return baked;
5328 }
5329
5330 // If atlas is locked, find closest match
5331 // FIXME-OPT: This is not an optimal query.
5332 if ((font->Flags & ImFontFlags_LockBakedSizes) || atlas->Locked)
5333 {
5334 baked = ImFontAtlasBakedGetClosestMatch(atlas, font, font_size, font_rasterizer_density);
5335 if (baked != NULL)
5336 return baked;
5337 if (atlas->Locked)
5338 {
5339 IM_ASSERT(!atlas->Locked && "Cannot use dynamic font size with a locked ImFontAtlas!"); // Locked because rendering backend does not support ImGuiBackendFlags_RendererHasTextures!
5340 return NULL;
5341 }
5342 }
5343
5344 // Create new
5345 baked = ImFontAtlasBakedAdd(atlas, font, font_size, font_rasterizer_density, baked_id);
5346 *p_baked_in_map = baked; // To avoid 'builder->BakedMap.SetVoidPtr(baked_id, baked);' while we can.
5347 return baked;
5348}

imgui_draw.cpp の 4315 行目に定義があります。

4316{
4317 IM_ASSERT(w > 0 && w <= 0xFFFF);
4318 IM_ASSERT(h > 0 && h <= 0xFFFF);
4319
4320 ImFontAtlasBuilder* builder = (ImFontAtlasBuilder*)atlas->Builder;
4321 const int pack_padding = atlas->TexGlyphPadding;
4322 builder->MaxRectSize.x = ImMax(builder->MaxRectSize.x, w);
4323 builder->MaxRectSize.y = ImMax(builder->MaxRectSize.y, h);
4324
4325 // Pack
4326 ImTextureRect r = { 0, 0, (unsigned short)w, (unsigned short)h };
4327 for (int attempts_remaining = 3; attempts_remaining >= 0; attempts_remaining--)
4328 {
4329 // Try packing
4330 stbrp_rect pack_r = {};
4331 pack_r.w = w + pack_padding;
4332 pack_r.h = h + pack_padding;
4333 stbrp_pack_rects((stbrp_context*)(void*)&builder->PackContext, &pack_r, 1);
4334 r.x = (unsigned short)pack_r.x;
4335 r.y = (unsigned short)pack_r.y;
4336 if (pack_r.was_packed)
4337 break;
4338
4339 // If we ran out of attempts, return fallback
4340 if (attempts_remaining == 0 || builder->LockDisableResize)
4341 {
4342 IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG_FONT("[font] Failed packing %dx%d rectangle. Returning fallback.\n", w, h);
4343 return ImFontAtlasRectId_Invalid;
4344 }
4345
4346 // Resize or repack atlas! (this should be a rare event)
4347 ImFontAtlasTextureMakeSpace(atlas);
4348 }
4349
4350 builder->MaxRectBounds.x = ImMax(builder->MaxRectBounds.x, r.x + r.w + pack_padding);
4351 builder->MaxRectBounds.y = ImMax(builder->MaxRectBounds.y, r.y + r.h + pack_padding);
4352 builder->RectsPackedCount++;
4353 builder->RectsPackedSurface += (w + pack_padding) * (h + pack_padding);
4354
4355 builder->Rects.push_back(r);
4356 if (overwrite_entry != NULL)
4357 return ImFontAtlasPackReuseRectEntry(atlas, overwrite_entry); // Write into an existing entry instead of adding one (used during repack)
4358 else
4359 return ImFontAtlasPackAllocRectEntry(atlas, builder->Rects.Size - 1);
4360}

IMGUI_API ImVec2i ImFontAtlasTextureGetSizeEstimate ( ImFontAtlas *  atlas)

imgui_draw.cpp の 4118 行目に定義があります。

4119{
4120 int min_w = ImUpperPowerOfTwo(atlas->TexMinWidth);
4121 int min_h = ImUpperPowerOfTwo(atlas->TexMinHeight);
4122 if (atlas->Builder == NULL || atlas->TexData == NULL || atlas->TexData->Status == ImTextureStatus_WantDestroy)
4123 return ImVec2i(min_w, min_h);
4124
4125 ImFontAtlasBuilder* builder = atlas->Builder;
4126 min_w = ImMax(ImUpperPowerOfTwo(builder->MaxRectSize.x), min_w);
4127 min_h = ImMax(ImUpperPowerOfTwo(builder->MaxRectSize.y), min_h);
4128 const int surface_approx = builder->RectsPackedSurface - builder->RectsDiscardedSurface; // Expected surface after repack
4129 const int surface_sqrt = (int)sqrtf((float)surface_approx);
4130
4131 int new_tex_w;
4132 int new_tex_h;
4133 if (min_w >= min_h)
4134 {
4135 new_tex_w = ImMax(min_w, ImUpperPowerOfTwo(surface_sqrt));
4136 new_tex_h = ImMax(min_h, (int)((surface_approx + new_tex_w - 1) / new_tex_w));
4137 if ((atlas->Flags & ImFontAtlasFlags_NoPowerOfTwoHeight) == 0)
4138 new_tex_h = ImUpperPowerOfTwo(new_tex_h);
4139 }
4140 else
4141 {
4142 new_tex_h = ImMax(min_h, ImUpperPowerOfTwo(surface_sqrt));
4143 if ((atlas->Flags & ImFontAtlasFlags_NoPowerOfTwoHeight) == 0)
4144 new_tex_h = ImUpperPowerOfTwo(new_tex_h);
4145 new_tex_w = ImMax(min_w, (int)((surface_approx + new_tex_h - 1) / new_tex_h));
4146 }
4147
4148 IM_ASSERT(ImIsPowerOfTwo(new_tex_w) && ImIsPowerOfTwo(new_tex_h));
4149 return ImVec2i(new_tex_w, new_tex_h);

IMGUI_API void ImFontAtlasUpdateNewFrame ( ImFontAtlas *  atlas,

imgui_draw.cpp の 2736 行目に定義があります。

2737{
2738 IM_ASSERT(atlas->Builder == NULL || atlas->Builder->FrameCount < frame_count); // Protection against being called twice.
2739 atlas->RendererHasTextures = renderer_has_textures;
2740
2741 // Check that font atlas was built or backend support texture reload in which case we can build now
2742 if (atlas->RendererHasTextures)
2743 {
2744 atlas->TexIsBuilt = true;
2745 if (atlas->Builder == NULL) // This will only happen if fonts were not already loaded.
2746 ImFontAtlasBuildMain(atlas);
2747 }
2748 else // Legacy backend
2749 {
2750 IM_ASSERT_USER_ERROR(atlas->TexIsBuilt, "Backend does not support ImGuiBackendFlags_RendererHasTextures, and font atlas is not built! Update backend OR make sure you called ImGui_ImplXXXX_NewFrame() function for renderer backend, which should call io.Fonts->GetTexDataAsRGBA32() / GetTexDataAsAlpha8().");
2751 }
2752 if (atlas->TexIsBuilt && atlas->Builder->PreloadedAllGlyphsRanges)
2753 IM_ASSERT_USER_ERROR(atlas->RendererHasTextures == false, "Called ImFontAtlas::Build() before ImGuiBackendFlags_RendererHasTextures got set! With new backends: you don't need to call Build().");
2754
2755 // Clear BakedCurrent cache, this is important because it ensure the uncached path gets taken once.
2756 // We also rely on ImFontBaked* pointers never crossing frames.
2757 ImFontAtlasBuilder* builder = atlas->Builder;
2758 builder->FrameCount = frame_count;
2759 for (ImFont* font : atlas->Fonts)
2760 font->LastBaked = NULL;
2761
2762 // Garbage collect BakedPool
2763 if (builder->BakedDiscardedCount > 0)
2764 {
2765 int dst_n = 0, src_n = 0;
2766 for (; src_n < builder->BakedPool.Size; src_n++)
2767 {
2768 ImFontBaked* p_src = &builder->BakedPool[src_n];
2769 if (p_src->WantDestroy)
2770 continue;
2771 ImFontBaked* p_dst = &builder->BakedPool[dst_n++];
2772 if (p_dst == p_src)
2773 continue;
2774 memcpy(p_dst, p_src, sizeof(ImFontBaked));
2775 builder->BakedMap.SetVoidPtr(p_dst->BakedId, p_dst);
2776 }
2777 IM_ASSERT(dst_n + builder->BakedDiscardedCount == src_n);
2778 builder->BakedPool.Size -= builder->BakedDiscardedCount;
2779 builder->BakedDiscardedCount = 0;
2780 }
2781
2782 // Update texture status
2783 for (int tex_n = 0; tex_n < atlas->TexList.Size; tex_n++)
2784 {
2785 ImTextureData* tex = atlas->TexList[tex_n];
2786 bool remove_from_list = false;
2787 if (tex->Status == ImTextureStatus_OK)
2788 {
2789 tex->Updates.resize(0);
2790 tex->UpdateRect.x = tex->UpdateRect.y = (unsigned short)~0;
2791 tex->UpdateRect.w = tex->UpdateRect.h = 0;
2792 }
2793 if (tex->Status == ImTextureStatus_WantCreate && atlas->RendererHasTextures)
2794 IM_ASSERT(tex->TexID == ImTextureID_Invalid && tex->BackendUserData == NULL && "Backend set texture's TexID/BackendUserData but did not update Status to OK.");
2795
2796 if (tex->Status == ImTextureStatus_Destroyed)
2797 {
2798 IM_ASSERT(tex->TexID == ImTextureID_Invalid && tex->BackendUserData == NULL && "Backend set texture Status to Destroyed but did not clear TexID/BackendUserData!");
2799 if (tex->WantDestroyNextFrame)
2800 remove_from_list = true; // Destroy was scheduled by us
2801 else
2802 tex->Status = ImTextureStatus_WantCreate; // Destroy was done was backend (e.g. freed resources mid-run)
2803 }
2804 else if (tex->WantDestroyNextFrame && tex->Status != ImTextureStatus_WantDestroy)
2805 {
2806 // Request destroy. Keep bool as it allows us to keep track of things.
2807 // We don't destroy pixels right away, as backend may have an in-flight copy from RAM.
2808 IM_ASSERT(tex->Status == ImTextureStatus_OK || tex->Status == ImTextureStatus_WantCreate || tex->Status == ImTextureStatus_WantUpdates);
2809 tex->Status = ImTextureStatus_WantDestroy;
2810 }
2811
2812 // The backend may need defer destroying by a few frames, to handle texture used by previous in-flight rendering.
2813 // We allow the texture staying in _WantDestroy state and increment a counter which the backend can use to take its decision.
2814 if (tex->Status == ImTextureStatus_WantDestroy)
2815 tex->UnusedFrames++;
2816
2817 // If a texture has never reached the backend, they don't need to know about it.
2818 if (tex->Status == ImTextureStatus_WantDestroy && tex->TexID == ImTextureID_Invalid && tex->BackendUserData == NULL)
2819 remove_from_list = true;
2820
2821 // Destroy and remove
2822 if (remove_from_list)
2823 {
2824 tex->DestroyPixels();
2825 IM_DELETE(tex);
2826 atlas->TexList.erase(atlas->TexList.begin() + tex_n);
2827 tex_n--;
2828 }
2829 }
2830}

#define ImTextureID_Invalid

2544 // Copy at most 'len' bytes, stop copying at 0 or past in_text_end. Branch predictor does a good job here,
2545 // so it is fast even with excessive branching.
2546 unsigned char s[4];
2547 s[0] = in_text + 0 < in_text_end ? in_text[0] : 0;
2548 s[1] = in_text + 1 < in_text_end ? in_text[1] : 0;
2549 s[2] = in_text + 2 < in_text_end ? in_text[2] : 0;
2550 s[3] = in_text + 3 < in_text_end ? in_text[3] : 0;
2551
2552 // Assume a four-byte character and load four bytes. Unused bits are shifted out.
2553 *out_char = (uint32_t)(s[0] & masks[len]) << 18;
2554 *out_char |= (uint32_t)(s[1] & 0x3f) << 12;
2555 *out_char |= (uint32_t)(s[2] & 0x3f) << 6;
2556 *out_char |= (uint32_t)(s[3] & 0x3f) << 0;
2557 *out_char >>= shiftc[len];
2558
2559 // Accumulate the various error conditions.
2560 int e = 0;
2561 e = (*out_char < mins[len]) << 6; // non-canonical encoding
2562 e |= ((*out_char >> 11) == 0x1b) << 7; // surrogate half?
2563 e |= (*out_char > IM_UNICODE_CODEPOINT_MAX) << 8; // out of range we can store in ImWchar (FIXME: May evolve)
2564 e |= (s[1] & 0xc0) >> 2;
2565 e |= (s[2] & 0xc0) >> 4;
2566 e |= (s[3] ) >> 6;
2567 e ^= 0x2a; // top two bits of each tail byte correct?
2568 e >>= shifte[len];
2569
2570 if (e)
2571 {
2572 // No bytes are consumed when *in_text == 0 || in_text == in_text_end.
2573 // One byte is consumed in case of invalid first byte of in_text.
2574 // All available bytes (at most `len` bytes) are consumed on incomplete/invalid second to last bytes.
2575 // Invalid or incomplete input may consume less bytes than wanted, therefore every byte has to be inspected in s.
2576 wanted = ImMin(wanted, !!s[0] + !!s[1] + !!s[2] + !!s[3]);
2577 *out_char = IM_UNICODE_CODEPOINT_INVALID;
2578 }
2579
2580 return wanted;
2581}

参照先 IM_UNICODE_CODEPOINT_INVALID, IM_UNICODE_CODEPOINT_MAX, ImMin().

参照元 ImGuiIO::AddInputCharactersUTF8(), ImFontGlyphRangesBuilder::AddText(), ImFont::CalcTextSizeA(), ImFont::CalcWordWrapPosition(), ImGui::DebugTextEncoding(), ImStb::IMSTB_TEXTEDIT_GETNEXTCHARINDEX_IMPL(), ImTextCountCharsFromUtf8(), ImTextCountUtf8BytesFromChar(), ImTextStrFromUtf8(), InputTextCalcTextSize(), ImGui::InputTextEx(), ImStb::is_word_boundary_from_left(), ImStb::is_word_boundary_from_right(), ImFont::RenderText(), ImStb::STB_TEXTEDIT_GETWIDTH() (計15項目).
